---
title: Formatting and linting Python code
description: When writing or editing Python code (`*.py`), ALWAYS run the code formatter the linter, and the type checker.
---

- To format code, run `uv run ruff format`.
- To lint code, run `uv run ruff check --fix`.
- Fix any linting errors before continuing.
- To run the type checker, run `uv run mypy`.
- Fix any typing errors before continuing.
